00:04:12.840 --> 00:04:17.210
embodies one of our
more recent initiatives.

00:04:17.210 --> 00:04:19.230
Another law that we have that --

00:04:19.230 --> 00:04:23.660
that the Library of Congress has
is called the American Television

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:26.010
and Radio Archive Act.

00:04:26.010 --> 00:04:30.740
It was part of the
Copyright Act of 1976.

00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:33.980
It mandates that the
Library of Congress establish

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:39.430
and grow an American
television and radio archive.

00:04:39.430 --> 00:04:44.810
We've recently expanded the
regulations governing that act

00:04:44.810 --> 00:04:49.060
to include a unique
authority to be able

00:04:49.060 --> 00:04:56.020
to capture unpublished audio-visual
transmissions from any format,

00:04:56.020 --> 00:05:01.870
from any venue, whether satellite,
cable, off-air, off-Internet,

00:05:01.870 --> 00:05:04.830
satellite radio, FM radio.

00:05:04.830 --> 00:05:10.700
And a number of years ago we began
capturing political talk radio,

00:05:10.700 --> 00:05:15.200 position:56%
