findings that many recordings

00:12:32.990 --> 00:12:35.770
of radio broadcasts
were untraceable,

00:12:35.770 --> 00:12:38.010
and numerous transcription
discs of national

00:12:38.010 --> 00:12:40.830
and local broadcasts
had been destroyed.

00:12:40.830 --> 00:12:43.910
And that little was known
of what still existed,

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:46.540
where it was stored,
and in what condition.

00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:52.260
A year later, a key
recommendation was

00:12:52.260 --> 00:12:55.120
to implement the Radio
Preservation Task Force.

00:12:55.120 --> 00:12:58.600
And this was formed in 2014
to spearhead the effort

00:12:58.600 --> 00:13:01.740
to identify challenges and
develop strategies to collect

00:13:01.740 --> 00:13:06.210
and preserve American radio
broadcasts and content.

00:13:06.210 --> 00:13:11.160
And in 2016 the Taskforce convened
its first National Conference.

00:13:11.160 --> 00:13:13.510
