00:14:01.530 --> 00:14:04.250
the <i>Post </i>article yesterday.

00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:07.160
We know that radio, like
film, has played a vital role

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:09.680
in the last hundred
years of our history.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:12.310
From the mid-1920s until the '50s,

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:14.500
radio was the nation's
preeminent source

00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:17.350
of entertainment and
news information.

00:14:17.350 --> 00:14:22.080
And today, despite the multiplicity
of generations, options, devices,

00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:25.990
and platforms, there are still
more than 14,000 radio stations

00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:29.850
in the United States, and radio's
still a major source of information

00:14:29.850 --> 00:14:33.420
that 93% of us listen
to, even millennials.

00:14:33.420 --> 00:14:36.420
I was surprised -- 91%.

00:14:36.420 --> 00:14:40.430
Radio is an irreplaceable part
from a sociocultural heritage,

00:14:40.430 --> 00:14:43.970
a key part of a social
memory, an ubiquitous,

00:14:43.970 --> 00:14:47.670
if perhaps underappreciated,
force in our daily lives.

00:14:47.670 --> 00:14:53.010
As you all know much better than I
do, and I appreciate your patience,

00:14:53.010 --> 00:14:57.060
radio preservation
presents unique challenges.

00:14:57.060 --> 00:15:00.620
The magnitude of the material
produced, it's a femoral nature,

00:15:00.620 --> 00:15:03.520
the deregulation and
consolidation of radio stations,

00:15:03.520 --> 00:15:06.490
the lack of technology to
preserve early broadcasts,

00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:09.680
general institutional
neglect, emerging formats,

00:15:09.680 --> 00:15:11.260
and underrepresentation
of diverse [inaudible],

00:15:11.260 --> 00:15:16.050
are all contributing factors in
the crisis facing the preservation

00:15:16.050 --> 00:15:17.610
of America's radio heritage.

00:15:17.610 --> 00:15:22.740 position:56%
So much was never captured, and
much that was has since disappeared.

00:15:22.740 --> 00:15:28.040
Our preservation consciousness
has, of course,

00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:30.060
been raised in recent
decades, and many libraries

00:15:30.060 --> 00:15:31.620
and archives have acquired
collections

00:15:31.620 --> 00:15:33.420
