00:26:56.330 --> 00:26:58.930
through the lens of
their own language.

00:26:58.930 --> 00:27:01.890
It can provide news from
the Native point of view,

00:27:01.890 --> 00:27:07.680
and health programs focusing on
local issues and local needs.

00:27:07.680 --> 00:27:11.610
It can broadcast music and culture
programs that support traditional

00:27:11.610 --> 00:27:13.970
and nontraditional Native artists.

00:27:13.970 --> 00:27:22.280
In 2013, Peggy Berryhill, a 42-year
veteran radio producer stated,

00:27:22.280 --> 00:27:25.050
"We love Native radio."

00:27:26.580 --> 00:27:29.270
Announcers sound like us.

00:27:29.270 --> 00:27:30.600
We hear the latest music.

00:27:30.600 --> 00:27:32.220
