01:10:00.250 --> 01:10:05.920
And in addition to the 40
episodes that are in English,

01:10:05.920 --> 01:10:09.160
20 of them were also in Spanish,

01:10:09.160 --> 01:10:11.810
because as I mentioned
several times,

01:10:11.810 --> 01:10:14.320
we are a hemispheric organization.

01:10:14.320 --> 01:10:19.180
We represent and collect --

01:10:19.180 --> 01:10:21.860
people, Native people of the
entire Western Hemisphere,

01:10:21.860 --> 01:10:23.210
including Hawaii.

01:10:23.210 --> 01:10:26.690
We don't actually collect Hawaiian
materials, but we do programming

01:10:26.690 --> 01:10:30.180
about Hawaiian, Native
Hawaiian people.

01:10:30.180 --> 01:10:36.920
So that program, <i>Living Voices</i>
, is freely available online.

01:10:36.920 --> 01:10:38.220
You can listen to it.

01:10:38.220 --> 01:10:41.110
You can buy CDs or
DV -- no, not DVDs.

01:10:41.110 --> 01:10:43.310
Just CDs of it.

01:10:43.310 --> 01:10:45.240
But the original recordings

01:10:45.240 --> 01:10:48.190
and the production
materials are also available.

01:10:48.190 --> 01:10:54.040
I mean, obviously, these
are in-depth interviews

01:10:54.040 --> 01:10:55.340
that were edited down.

01:10:55.340 --> 01:10:57.860
That's sort of the nature
of media production.

01:10:57.860 --> 01:11:02.030
So we are aware, as an institution,

01:11:02.030 --> 01:11:04.840
of the value of broadcasting,
of the value of radio.

01:11:04.840 --> 01:11:08.380
It isn't an area that
we have collected

01:11:08.380 --> 01:11:10.000
with a great deal of focus.

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:13.130
But I ask all of you,
